Class SimpleCsvListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.uima.aae.client.UimaAsBaseCallbackListener

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.uima.aae.client.UimaASStatusCallbackListener

    public class SimpleCsvListener
extends BaseCsvListener
    Note: This is a very simple gov.va.vinci.leo.listener to output one type of annotation and, optionally, its features. It DOES NOT work well with features of Array type. If you need to output features of Array type, this code simply calls toStringArray on the ArrayFS, and outputs those values.
    Author:
    vhaislcornir

        Constructor that sets the initial outputFile, annotation type name for output, and includeFeatures flag.
        Parameters:
        outputFile - File to which the annotation information will be output.
        includeHeaders - If true, a header line will be written out first.
        delimeter - the csv delimeter (comma, tab, etc...)
        includeFeatures - If true then include the features that need to be added.
        typeName - Name of the annotation type that will be output to the file. At least one type name is required.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is an error writing to the file.
